    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Routing Between Claude and GPT from Mobile"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world AI-powered mobile apps often need more than one model. Claude excels at careful reasoning, nuanced instruction-following, and long-context document analysis. GPT-4o is competitive for code generation and creative writing. Gemini handles multimodal inputs natively. Rather than committing to one model for all tasks, you can build a routing layer \u2014 a backend proxy that inspects each request and forwards it to the most suitable model. The mobile app sees a single unified API and a consistent response shape regardless of which LLM ran underneath."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Multi-model router architecture: Mobile App \u2192 Router/Proxy \u2192 Claude / GPT-4o / Gemini \u2192 normalized response",
          "title": "Routing layer between mobile app and multiple LLMs"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why a Proxy, Not Direct Client-Side Routing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The routing logic and API keys belong on the backend, not in the mobile bundle. Client-side routing would expose multiple API keys in the app binary, leak your cost strategy, and require an app update every time you adjust routing rules. A backend proxy keeps secrets secret, lets you change routing rules instantly without redeployment, and gives you a single log stream across all models for debugging and cost tracking."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Unified Request Contract"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Define a single request shape the mobile app always sends. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "taskType"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field is the primary routing signal; the optional "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "preferredModel"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " lets power users override the default route:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Shared types \u2014 used by both mobile app and backend\nexport type TaskType =\n  | 'analysis'       // \u2192 Claude (careful reasoning)\n  | 'creative'       // \u2192 GPT-4o\n  | 'code'           // \u2192 GPT-4o\n  | 'multimodal'     // \u2192 Gemini\n  | 'general';       // \u2192 cheapest available\n\nexport type ModelId = 'claude-opus-4-8' | 'gpt-4o' | 'gemini-1.5-pro';\n\nexport interface ChatRequest {\n  messages: Array<{ role: 'user' | 'assistant'; content: string }>;\n  taskType: TaskType;\n  preferredModel?: ModelId;   // optional override\n  maxTokens?: number;         // default: 1024\n}\n\nexport interface ChatResponse {\n  text: string;\n  model: ModelId;             // which model actually ran\n  inputTokens: number;\n  outputTokens: number;\n  latencyMs: number;\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Routing Logic (Backend)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The router runs a simple decision tree. More sophisticated apps can replace this with a trained text classifier or A/B experiment buckets:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// router.ts (Node.js / Hono / Express)\nimport Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk';\nimport OpenAI from 'openai';\nimport { GoogleGenerativeAI } from '@google/generative-ai';\n\nconst anthropic = new Anthropic();\nconst openai = new OpenAI();\nconst google = new GoogleGenerativeAI(process.env.GOOGLE_API_KEY!);\n\nfunction selectModel(req: ChatRequest): ModelId {\n  if (req.preferredModel) return req.preferredModel;\n  switch (req.taskType) {\n    case 'analysis':   return 'claude-opus-4-8';\n    case 'creative':   return 'gpt-4o';\n    case 'code':       return 'gpt-4o';\n    case 'multimodal': return 'gemini-1.5-pro';\n    case 'general':    return 'claude-opus-4-8';  // default\n    default:           return 'claude-opus-4-8';\n  }\n}\n\nasync function callClaude(\n  req: ChatRequest, maxTokens: number\n): Promise<ChatResponse> {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  const msg = await anthropic.messages.create({\n    model: 'claude-opus-4-8',\n    max_tokens: maxTokens,\n    messages: req.messages,\n  });\n  return {\n    text: msg.content[0].type === 'text' ? msg.content[0].text : '',\n    model: 'claude-opus-4-8',\n    inputTokens: msg.usage.input_tokens,\n    outputTokens: msg.usage.output_tokens,\n    latencyMs: Date.now() - start,\n  };\n}\n\nasync function callGpt(\n  req: ChatRequest, maxTokens: number\n): Promise<ChatResponse> {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  const msg = await openai.chat.completions.create({\n    model: 'gpt-4o',\n    max_tokens: maxTokens,\n    messages: req.messages as any,\n  });\n  return {\n    text: msg.choices[0].message.content ?? '',\n    model: 'gpt-4o',\n    inputTokens: msg.usage?.prompt_tokens ?? 0,\n    outputTokens: msg.usage?.completion_tokens ?? 0,\n    latencyMs: Date.now() - start,\n  };\n}\n\nexport async function route(req: ChatRequest): Promise<ChatResponse> {\n  const model = selectModel(req);\n  const maxTokens = req.maxTokens ?? 1024;\n  try {\n    if (model === 'claude-opus-4-8') return await callClaude(req, maxTokens);\n    if (model === 'gpt-4o')         return await callGpt(req, maxTokens);\n    throw new Error(`Unsupported model: ${model}`);\n  } catch (err: any) {\n    // Fallback: if GPT fails, try Claude; if Claude fails, try GPT\n    if (model === 'gpt-4o') return await callClaude(req, maxTokens);\n    if (model === 'claude-opus-4-8') return await callGpt(req, maxTokens);\n    throw err;\n  }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Mobile App Side"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The React Native component knows nothing about which model runs. It classifies the task, sends to the proxy, and displays both the response text and a model attribution badge:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { useState } from 'react';\nimport type { ChatRequest, ChatResponse, TaskType } from './types';\n\nconst API_BASE = 'https://your-api.com';\n\nasync function sendMessage(\n  messages: ChatRequest['messages'],\n  taskType: TaskType\n): Promise<ChatResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/chat`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ messages, taskType } satisfies ChatRequest),\n  });\n  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`API error: ${res.status}`);\n  return res.json() as Promise<ChatResponse>;\n}\n\n// Heuristic task classifier \u2014 runs on device, no extra API call\nfunction classifyTask(text: string): TaskType {\n  const lower = text.toLowerCase();\n  if (/\\bcode\\b|function|implement|debug|refactor/.test(lower)) return 'code';\n  if (/\\banalyz|compare|reason|explain why|break down/.test(lower)) return 'analysis';\n  if (/\\bwrite a\\b|poem|story|creative|blog/.test(lower)) return 'creative';\n  return 'general';\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model Attribution Badge"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Show users which model answered their question. This builds trust and helps them understand when to use the model selector override:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "tsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "const MODEL_LABELS: Record<string, { label: string; color: string }> = {\n  'claude-opus-4-8': { label: 'Claude', color: '#6d28d9' },\n  'gpt-4o':          { label: 'GPT-4o', color: '#059669' },\n  'gemini-1.5-pro':  { label: 'Gemini', color: '#b91c1c' },\n};\n\nfunction ModelBadge({ model }: { model: string }) {\n  const info = MODEL_LABELS[model] ?? { label: model, color: '#6b7280' };\n  return (\n    <View style={[\n      styles.badge,\n      { borderColor: info.color, backgroundColor: info.color + '18' },\n    ]}>\n      <Text style={[styles.badgeText, { color: info.color }]}>\n        via {info.label}\n      </Text>\n    </View>\n  );\n}\n\n// Inside the message bubble:\n{message.model && <ModelBadge model={message.model} />}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Conversation Continuity Across Models"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Anthropic and OpenAI message formats are nearly identical \u2014 both use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{ role, content }"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " arrays \u2014 so conversation history can be forwarded to either model unchanged. This lets the router switch models mid-conversation without losing context:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// All history is stored in the universal format:\ntype Message = { role: 'user' | 'assistant'; content: string };\n\n// On each new message:\nasync function handleSend(input: string) {\n  const taskType = classifyTask(input);\n  const userMsg: Message = { role: 'user', content: input };\n  const history = [...messages, userMsg];  // full conversation\n\n  const response = await sendMessage(history, taskType);\n\n  // Add assistant message to history (model label kept separately)\n  setMessages([...history, { role: 'assistant', content: response.text }]);\n  setModelHistory(prev => [...prev, response.model]);\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Context continuity caveat: "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Claude's extended thinking and Sonnet-level instruction-following capabilities do not carry over to a GPT conversation mid-thread. If the task switches models, users may notice subtle differences in tone or depth. Make routing switches explicit to users if continuity matters."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model Selector UI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Give power users a manual override so they can explicitly choose Claude for sensitive or complex tasks:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "tsx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { useState } from 'react';\nimport { View, Text, Pressable, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';\nimport type { ModelId } from './types';\n\nconst MODELS: Array<{ id: ModelId | 'auto'; label: string }> = [\n  { id: 'auto',           label: 'Auto' },\n  { id: 'claude-opus-4-8', label: 'Claude' },\n  { id: 'gpt-4o',         label: 'GPT-4o' },\n];\n\nfunction ModelPicker({\n  selected,\n  onChange,\n}: {\n  selected: ModelId | 'auto';\n  onChange: (m: ModelId | 'auto') => void;\n}) {\n  return (\n    <View style={styles.picker}>\n      {MODELS.map(m => (\n        <Pressable\n          key={m.id}\n          onPress={() => onChange(m.id)}\n          style={[\n            styles.chip,\n            selected === m.id && styles.chipActive,\n          ]}\n        >\n          <Text style={[\n            styles.chipText,\n            selected === m.id && styles.chipTextActive,\n          ]}>{m.label}</Text>\n        </Pressable>\n      ))}\n    </View>\n  );\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
