        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Cost-aware routing in the router\nfunction estimateTokens(messages: ChatRequest['messages']): number {\n  return messages.reduce((sum, m) => sum + m.content.length / 4, 0);\n}\n\nfunction selectModelWithBudget(req: ChatRequest): ModelId {\n  const tokens = estimateTokens(req.messages);\n\n  // For 'general' tasks under 200 tokens, use the cheapest option\n  if (req.taskType === 'general' && tokens < 200) {\n    return 'claude-opus-4-8';  // or route to claude-haiku-4-5 if wired up\n  }\n  return selectModel(req);\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "System prompt compatibility. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Claude and GPT handle system prompts differently. Claude prefers them as a separate "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "system"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " parameter; GPT accepts "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "{ role: 'system', content: '...' }"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " as the first message. Your router must translate the system prompt appropriately for each model."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Streaming normalization. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Anthropic streams "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "content_block_delta"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " events; OpenAI streams "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "choices[].delta.content"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " events. If you want streaming through the proxy, normalize both into a common SSE format before forwarding to the client."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Task classifier accuracy. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A regex-based classifier will misroute edge cases (\"analyze this poem\" hits 'analysis' but is also 'creative'). Consider running a cheap fast model as the classifier itself, or let users override freely."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Infinite fallback loops. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The fallback chain (GPT fails \u2192 try Claude) must not loop. Add a "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "alreadyFailed"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " flag or a maximum retry counter to the route function to prevent infinite retries."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Token count mismatch. "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Claude counts tokens differently from GPT. A response that fits in GPT's 4096-token output budget may exceed Claude's (or vice versa). Use the model's actual token limit \u2014 not a shared constant \u2014 in the router."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep all routing logic and API keys on the backend. The mobile app calls a single endpoint with a task type and gets back a normalized response."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A simple rule-based router (analysis \u2192 Claude, code \u2192 GPT-4o) handles most apps; replace with a classifier model or A/B system as needs grow."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Claude and OpenAI share the same "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "{ role, content }"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " message format, so conversation history can be forwarded between models without conversion."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Show a model attribution badge in the chat UI so users know which model answered and can override with the model picker."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add a fallback chain so that if your primary model's API is down, requests gracefully degrade to the secondary model rather than returning an error."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}